  "text": "where S is the ratio of one loaded surface to the forcefree surface and β is a numerical constant. For rubbers that are square, circular or moderately rectangular in cross-section β = 2 should be used and for rubbers with the addition of carbon black, somewhat smaller values should be used [CITATION_1] . For very large shape factors S some contribution to the total deflection may be anticipated from the bulk compression of the rubber. To account for this, Gent and Lindley [CITATION_2] derived the equation:",
